  "description": "ORGANISM's cellular automata audio output feeds OPAL's grain buffer via AudioToWavetable. The cellular patterns — emergent, aperiodic, structurally complex — become the source material for granulation at 200ms Hann window grains, density=22. ORGANISM's rule-set generates audio that was never composed; OPAL granularizes that unplanned material at human-scale timing. RhythmToBlend coupling from ORGANISM drives opal_density modulation — cell birth/death rates directly pulse the grain scheduler. Colony breath as grain rhythm.",
